The paper deals with communication networks and network coding, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses a layering procedure, which is a common technique in computer networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions a duality for linear network codes, which is a concept in algebraic coding theory (cs.DC) and communication complexity (cs.CC).
